          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            Surely Bayern will rest Lewandowski. I'm not sure why he played midweek given Munich had guaranteed themselves top spot. Pep has been reading Arsene Wenger's book on needlessly risking key players. The league is also won so it makes sense to rest him here. I know people like to think it isn't done-and-dusted but before the BMG game, Bayern were 1/50 (on average based on 21 non-German bookmakers) to win the league. After LOSING to BMG and Dortmund beating Wolfsburg, they are now averaged at 1/55! You know it's seen as a dead cert if you're more likely to win the league after a loss and a rival's win than before- despite being only 5 points ahead. Even with the winter break, you don't want the most potent #9 in world football to go into it with an injury. There's a big difference between resting over winter & recovering. For this game I'm going with a 2-0 Bayern win, regardless of who plays. Ingolstadt will defend in numbers as is the norm at the Allianz but Bayern have too much.

            5 years ago
